            {
                "s2_paper_id": "ff4b9c9033a2188e33873ab3a64788798b2c68db",
                "title": "Towards a Channel Model for Microfilm",
                "year": 2008,
                "venue": "Archiving Conference",
                "citation_count": 10,
                "reference_count": 6,
                "abstract": "Technological advance causes obsolescence and unpredictable lifetimes of digital storage media and systems. We present PEVIAR, a digital archival solution based on microfilm that offers superior lifetime and independence from proprietary hardware and software technologies. Digital data is to be stored as a 2-dimensional raster image. In order to determine the technical parameters of our system, we carry out an investigation of the device setup given by a recorder, the film itself and a scanner. We measure the modulation transfer function of these components and the granularity of the film material. We also propose a 2-dimensional channel model incorporating intersymbol interference. From our examinations we conclude that a resolution of 8\u00b5m can be achieved.",
